Rutulis, dative, ‘ over the Rutuli? The war with Turnus, king of the Rutuli, forms the subject of the later books of the Aeneid, and his death by the sword of Aeneas concludes the poem.

267. Iulo, dative by attraction to cui. Cp. ‘cui nomen asilo ' G. 3. 347. The identification of Ascanius, as Iulus, with the Dardan Ilus and the descent from him of the Gens Iulia (l. 288) was a favoni-ite Roman fiction, supported of course by the Julian family and its adherents.
